Setting up a [[dwarf multicannon]] in the instance will result in the message {{mes|It's far too muddy for you to set up a cannon here.}}

Brutus drops [[logs]] and [[oak logs]] quite often, as well as at least one guaranteed [[raw t-bone steak]] each kill. Bringing a [[tinderbox]] (with 15 [[Firemaking]] for oak logs) can be helpful to burn logs and cook steaks between kills, allowing for several back-to-back kills even if taking damage each kill. The altar in the [[Lumbridge church]] can be used to restore prayer as well.

===Safespot cycle===
[[File:Brutus safespot cycle.mp4|thumb|400px|A player demonstrates the perpetual safespot cycle for Brutus.]]
Brutus cannot be [[Flinching|flinched]], but can be temporarily [[safespot]]ted using nearby scenery, such as the plants and [[Warning Sign (Brutus)|warning sign]].

However, if the player is out of Brutus' attack range for 15 ticks (9s), he may use his charge attack to reach the player which can pass through obstacles, or he will exclaim {{overhead|*huff*}} and move around obstacles to reach the player.
As such, lower levels may wish to utilise a set of safespots; with this method, players can avoid all attacks from Brutus. This method starts with tile 1 and as soon as Brutus moves, run to tile 2, etc.
